{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d87846e7-a5f4-45b5-be16-84017724c627","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked via `dotnet run`. When you use `dotnet run`, the test process stays alive and watches for code changes, re-running affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` runs tests to completion and exits — it doesn't support the hot reload loop.\n\nSo your workflow is:\n\n```bash\n# Set the env var (if not already done)\nexport TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1\n\n# Run with hot reload\ndotnet run\n```\n\nThen edit your test or source files, and the runner will automatically rebuild and re-execute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"696bc3b5-f048-47bb-bc1e-6d5c262396b2","outputTokens":170,"requestId":"0BCC:318D8B:6EC2A7:80CE7D:69F010C3"},"id":"a53b265b-16fa-4e8f-a739-b7b1760d4416","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:43:36.943Z","parentId":"dc325b59-4f12-40a6-ad93-d710913f8f4d"}
